IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: During the month of January 2023 members of DCNTF began an investigation into Dwayne Lemont ELLIOTT Sr for the distribution of CDS within Dorchester County, Maryland. I request this case remain open pending further investigation. Supplements will be uploaded to this case file accordingly.

On April 17, 2023 members of the Dorchester County Narcotics Task Force hereinafter referred to as DCNTF received a phone call from the Cambridge Police Department in reference to a search and seizure warrant executed on ELLIOTTs vehicle. Cambridge Police Dept. advised they received a call for service at 623 Douglas Street, Cambridge, Dorchester County, Maryland in reference to an assault between Dwayne ELLIOTT and Heather ELLIOTT. Cambridge Police advised they had enough evidence to charge ELLIOTT with a domestic violence crime. Further investigation by Cambridge Police Dept revealed enough probable cause in order to execute a search and seizure warrant on a vehicle in which ELLIOTT utilizes on a daily basis. Cambridge Police Dept advised during the search warrant of the vehicle, they seized a large amount of Heroin/Fentanyl as well as a stolen firearm. Due to an ongoing CDS investigation by members of DCNTF into ELLIOTT distributing large amounts of CDS, TFC Frock responded to the area and met with members of the Cambridge Police Dept. On April 17, 2023 TFC Frock authored a search and seizure warrant for the residence of 623 Douglas Street, Cambridge, Dorchester County, Maryland. The warrant was presented to the Honorable Judge Jones of the Circuit Court of Dorchester County, Maryland and was signed on April 17, 2023. At approximately 1530 hours on April 17, 2023 the search and seizure warrant was executed at the above listed address. It should be noted that Cambridge Police Dept was already in contact with Heather Elliott who was within the residence at the time of the search warrant. At that time, a systematic search of the residence was conducted. Investigators were able to identify the residence to have a living room, a kitchen and a bathroom located on the first floor. The second floor was identified to contain two bedrooms. Each bedroom was identified by numbers starting with bedroom #1 which was identified to be directly across from the stairwell. Bedroom #2 was identified to be on the right side of the hallway. During the search of the residence, investigators located a small orange pill bottle located within the TV stand in the living room. Within the orange pill bottle, investigators observed a clear plastic baggie containing Cocaine (Item #1). Investigators then located a dark colored bag containing 36 9mm bullets within the closet area of bedroom #2 (Item #2). During the search warrant, Heather Elliott made comments stating that she deleted all the evidence that she showed CPD in reference to ELLIOTT manufacturing CDS within the residence. At that time, Heather ELLIOTT gave consent to search through her phone by signature which was captured on the Maryland State Police consent search form. At which time, Heather Elliotts Iphone was seized (Item #3). No other evidence was seized during the search and seizure warrant. Heather Elliott was provided a copy of the search warrant and was provided the evidence form log which indicated the items being seized from the residence. All evidence was seized and secured per the Maryland State Police Policy and Procedures. At that time, Item #1 was weighed which produced a weight of .7 grams of Cocaine which was verified by Sgt. Tyler of DCNTF. TFC Frock requests this case remain open pending the search of Heather Elliotts cellular phone. Each and all events occurred in Dorchester County, Maryland. See Cambridge Police Dept reports in reference to the call for service and search and seizure warrant of the vehicle.

I request this case be closed due to the Cambridge Police Dept arresting Elliott on other CDS charges. TFC Frock then made contact with the Dorchester County States Attorneys Office in reference to the Cocaine which as seized during the search and seizure warrant. Due to the amount of Heroin/Fentanyl seized by Cambridge Police Dept, no further charges will be placed on ELLIOTT for the Cocaine seized from the residence. Case closed.
